<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-4D0D68A4-09BC-4ECD-A279-89F6E59CE58E" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-4D0D68A4-09BC-4ECD-A279-89F6E59CE58E" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">06 How to adjust the position of the chiller (V2)</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Adjustment</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_A392D23B9FA5434A8095E72A33F001E1" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_BFC835835B5440A98A2DF72417BDB02D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> 13mm Spaner/Open End Wrench
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Positioning the chiller unit opposite the engine.</title><p class="- topic/p "> For print quality reasons the chiller unit has to be positioned loose, vibration-fee from the engine and covering. (The goal of this adjustment) 
</p><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the two POSITION JIGS (<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C</b>) from the ROLLER CART ASSY (<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A</b>) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5DECFC2A-3BAC-4617-806C-9F894284016D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9F4686D0-1DA5-4A39-BB6F-FFEE63710439-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9F4686D0-1DA5-4A39-BB6F-FFEE63710439-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-A03FDA47-3741-49E5-AB8B-C05AE552AA81" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3ABC5227-122B-4EA1-AF78-9C1DE8327928-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3ABC5227-122B-4EA1-AF78-9C1DE8327928-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To make this adjustment more easily, first turn the FOOT LEVELING (3 turns cc) downwards till just above the floor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-1DD67701-EBE4-494E-B494-105A6D2A8DD2" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-481C6E02-7097-4533-8619-EC9E1C16B000-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-481C6E02-7097-4533-8619-EC9E1C16B000-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the chiller close to the engine. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Mount BRACKET REINFORCE CPL 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b> with the 2 screws 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(X)</b>. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E684A165-A215-4608-AB59-504CE66EC3FA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3CB1A010-20A1-4940-BD78-47A222E59239-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3CB1A010-20A1-4940-BD78-47A222E59239-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-0BC2720C-2450-43C0-A666-E41AA6E6A747" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9BC50447-10E7-4570-B8BD-F9CED917CC42-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9BC50447-10E7-4570-B8BD-F9CED917CC42-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Mount both BRACKET POSITIONING JIGS<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b>and BRACKET REINFORCE CPL 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b>. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-191114E1-7A8B-4330-A283-83F705CF5745" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-683A879A-BB6A-437F-A617-05FB8A55DC00-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-683A879A-BB6A-437F-A617-05FB8A55DC00-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-C68FD339-1C96-4581-AD83-26D9C3A9E23D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9294C202-D014-4CD2-B6A6-8091DEE3C642-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9294C202-D014-4CD2-B6A6-8091DEE3C642-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Position the chiller unit in X- and Y- direction: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">1 lip of BRACKET POSITIONING JIG<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b> hits ROLLER CART ASSY for positioning in X-direction. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Distance = 0 (+1/0) (2x) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The other lip sticks in a positioning gap (1 small and 1 slotted) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-81BA147A-87FF-48E3-B99E-2203546169A6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3B94EF92-7B9F-46D6-B898-434D200B57F5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3B94EF92-7B9F-46D6-B898-434D200B57F5-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-B2779171-3DED-4800-AA34-5E9F084D1A1A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DAFBA40B-FE9B-4B7E-BDBB-4FDEA78CC832-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DAFBA40B-FE9B-4B7E-BDBB-4FDEA78CC832-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Fix the chiller by screwing further down FOOT LEVELING 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(G) 
</b>(3 turns cc) till CASTORS 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(E)</b> (4x) are just (0,5 +3/0 mm) free from the floor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-97F79C36-3C05-45F4-B438-FD72D35D8F83" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-50EBCF53-DA58-4BBC-BE13-7C6100E6DCB9-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-50EBCF53-DA58-4BBC-BE13-7C6100E6DCB9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Fixate FOOT LEVELING 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(G)</b> (3 turns cw) with NUT (3x). 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Remove BRACKET POSITIONING JIGS<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> (C)</b> (2x) from BRACKET REINFORCE CPL<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> (D) 
</b>and mount them back on ROLLER CART ASSY 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b>. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-0B1BC475-DA86-4E35-AF78-8ED9885B10D7" class="- topic/fig "/><fig id="GUID-0C0BF9C5-628F-45B0-9455-6AC2AC7F052B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0EA0C7B8-42AA-41C9-813F-DE99FE14AB12-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0EA0C7B8-42AA-41C9-813F-DE99FE14AB12-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-72EBAA1A-9F5D-40EA-8CA4-6C80BF9A2B3E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4AF342FF-004D-42C5-BE11-F29743AC019D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4AF342FF-004D-42C5-BE11-F29743AC019D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-90AB4C18-0C86-4961-9753-9D2D314E5533.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Adjustment</linktext></link></linkpool><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-0CF1F378-65AF-4B46-B46E-82F7EE70A33A.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
